Thanks for the feedback!

There are two built in roles provided for CMS, which are ServerGroupAdministratorRole as well as ServerGroupreaderRole which is a safer option to assign to developers (referencing your scenario).&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Also, it is not really &quot;possible&quot; to use SQL authentication with CMS as it does not save credentials, whenever you connect to any server saved in CMS, your Windows Authenticated Credentials will be used.
